author: @francescaetc
text:
I feel like Google is progressively losing it's simple and practical ecosystem as we move forward, especially after this announcement. I think you are losing 99% of us who are savvy with technology, but not necessarily developing an AI tool or software program.This presentation overwhelms a viewer with their endless new tools and capabilities, all with different names, varying versions and no clear date on when any given tool might become available to the public for use. In stark contrast, Microsoft/Open AI's recent announcement for Chat GPT 4o was an easy to understand, streamlined, and optimized tool which users can interact with relatively easily across the many Microsoft Office Suite of tools and software. ONE tool versus 10.

I believe that what people want more than ever now is clear, concise, honest, simple, and highly cross-functional or multipurpose technology.
